Kathleen Sebelius

As Health and Human Services Secretary, Kathleen Sebelius was one of the key architects behind ObamaCare. Under her watch, ObamaCare failed to meet many deadlines. She oversaw the Healthcare.gov crash launched the exchange to the public before it was close to ready. After a tumultuous five year stint as Secretary, Sebelius finally stepped down.








