Kathleen Sebelius (/sᵻˈbiːliəs/; née Gilligan; born May 15, 1948) is an American politician who served as the 21st United States Secretary of Health and Human Services from 2009[1] until 2014.[2] Previously, she was the 44th Governor of Kansas from 2003 to 2009, the second woman to hold that office. She is a member of the Democratic Party. Sebelius was the Democratic respondent to the 2008 State of the Union address[3] and is chair-emerita of the Democratic Governors Association (she was its first female chair).[4] On April 10, 2014, Sebelius announced her resignation as Secretary of Health and Human Services.[2] She is CEO of Sebelius Resources LLC.[5]



